Singapore does not have the highest GDP per capita when considering nominal values; Monaco and Liechtenstein rank higher.
The claim 'Singapore has the highest GDP per capita' is context-dependent (PPP vs nominal), but even in PPP terms, the CIA data is an estimate and other sources may differ.
Given the lack of universal consensus and higher rankings for other nations in nominal terms, the absolute claim is false.
